			<td class="xar-norm message">
				<div class="xarbb-messagecontrols">
					<div class="leftnote"><span class="xar-sub">Posted Feb 08, 2011 at 10:44:11 PM</span></div>
										<div style="float: left;"><strong class="xar-sub">Subject: special ed  teacher pulling out general ed students
</strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div>
															<p>I am a special ed teacher that teaches the inclusion model at a middle school.  My general ed counterparts have asked me to pull out special ed students as well as general ed students to teach in my classroom 2x a week to work on reading comprehension. I am pretty sure that this is against the law, but cannot find it.  My question, what is the legal issue on this?  Is it illegal?<br />
Thanks!</p>
									</div>
							</td>
		</tr><tr>
			<td class="xar-norm author">
